  stimulus_text = 'While studying the history of the Civil War, a student discovered that in 1863, a Black man named Robert Smalls, who had escaped slavery, managed to steal a Confederate ship and sail it to Union forces. Smalls’s actions not only helped the Union win the war, but they also helped to inspire other enslaved people to fight for their freedom. Researchers note that the pattern described above remained consistent across repeated observations, suggesting the finding was not a one-time anomaly. They caution that local conditions can still vary, yet the overall relationship held in each documented case.',
