  correct_answer = 'C',
  explanation = 'The most effective way to combine the underlined sentences is to use the conjunction "which" to introduce a dependent clause that explains the effect of the printing press.  The conjunction "which" shows a cause-and-effect relationship between the printing press and the spread of literacy.  The other choices are less effective because they do not show this relationship as clearly. The passage states that "The invention of the printing press in the 15th century, which allowed for the mass production of books, was a significa…", which is the textual anchor for eliminating weaker choices. Choice C is correct because it aligns with that evidence: The printing press, however, made it possible to produce books more quickly and cheaply, which resul…. Each incorrect option either contradicts a explicit detail, imports information not present in the text, or answers a different question than the one asked.',
  source_metadata = COALESCE(source_metadata, '{}'::jsonb) || '{"section":"english","skill_id":"FSS","domain_id":"conventions","opensat_index":1162,"opensat_domain":"Standard English Conventions","opensat_raw_id":"89230131","opensat_difficulty":"Medium","english_content_v2":true,"english_content_upgraded_at":"2026-06-12T20:01:56.916Z","english_content_upgrade_method":"upgrade-english-content.mjs"}'::jsonb,
